               <msContents>
                  <summary>This complete copy of the <title>Dīvān</title> of Ḥāfiẓ (ca. 1315–1390)
                     contains most of the ghazal lyric poems and quatrains typically found in other
                     copies. It also features a lavishly illuminated opening folios, headers, and
                     margins. A scribe named <persName role="scr ato" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                        >Muḥammad ‘Alī Khvānsar</persName> completed this volume in <placeName
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001541" key="place_7001541"
                        >Hyderabad</placeName> at the <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                        when="1807-01-10">start of Ẕī al-Qa‘dah 1221 AH (early–mid Jan.
                        1807)</date>, for the British Resident at Hyderabad, <persName role="pat">
                        Thomas Sydenham (1780–1816)</persName>.</summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_50-item1">
                     <author key="person_56731778" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/56731778/"
                        change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥāfiẓ, 14th
                           cent.</persName>
