                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6835">34</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6749"
                           >262</ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6750">263</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6777"
                           >288</ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7061">563</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7351"
                           >842</ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26545">945</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26546"
                           >946</ref>, and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26520"
                           >1001–1003</ref> (3 vols). For another manuscript completed by the same
                        scribe for Sydenham held in the Rylands, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7203"><idno>Persian
                              MS 70</idno></ref>. For more on Sydenham, see Urban.</note>
                  </msItem>
